<subSubSection pageId="5" pageNumber="1643" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="5.[494,887,168,224]" box="[600,777,200,224]" pageId="5" pageNumber="1643">
(
<figureCitation box="[608,712,200,224]" captionStart="Figure 2" captionStartId="6.[146,213,1230,1252]" captionTargetBox="[155,1099,175,1194]" captionTargetId="figure-87@6.[146,1104,165,1194]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="Figure 2. (A–D) Zyzzogeton guatemalensis sp. nov., male holotype. (A) Pygofer, subgenital plate, and anal tube, lateral view. (B) Genital capsule, ventral view. (C) Connective and style, dorsal view. (D) Aedeagus, lateral view. (E–G) Zyzzogeton haenschi Breddin, female. (E) Abdominal sternite VII, ventral view. (F) Pygofer and anal tube, lateral view. (G) Second valvula of ovipositor, general lateral view. BHA: basal hyaline area, RPL: subrectangular pygofer lobe. (Scale bars: 1 mm.)" figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4593935" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4593935/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="1643">Figures 2</figureCitation>
A–D)
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="5.[213,340,280,304]" box="[213,340,280,304]" pageId="5" pageNumber="1643">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[213,340,280,304]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="1643">Description</emphasis>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="5.[213,289,320,344]" box="[213,289,320,344]" pageId="5" pageNumber="1643">
<emphasis box="[213,289,320,344]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="1643">Colour</emphasis>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="5.[213,1169,360,544]" pageId="5" pageNumber="1643">Dorsum and venter mostly brown to dark brown. Pronotum with pair of small yellow marks on anterior half near lateral margins, located just before conical protuberances, and pair of inconspicuous yellow marks at inner bases of conical protuberances. Forewings with irregular yellow maculae located mainly on clavus and also on small portions of discal and brachial cells on basal half of corium and inner anteapical and brachial cells on distal half of corium.</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="5.[213,291,587,611]" box="[213,291,587,611]" pageId="5" pageNumber="1643">
<emphasis box="[213,291,587,611]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="1643">Length</emphasis>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="5.[213,1169,626,714]" pageId="5" pageNumber="1643">
Length of male, 
<quantity box="[401,476,626,650]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.2" pageId="5" pageNumber="1643" unit="mm" value="22.0">22 mm</quantity>
(approximate value because the specimen was mounted with the left forewing spread and the right wing was removed and glued on a small piece of cardboard).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="5.[213,350,770,794]" box="[213,350,770,794]" pageId="5" pageNumber="1643">
<emphasis box="[213,350,770,794]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="1643">Morphology</emphasis>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="5.[213,1169,810,1026]" pageId="5" pageNumber="1643">
Head, thorax, and male genitalia (
<figureCitation box="[613,717,810,834]" captionStart="Figure 2" captionStartId="6.[146,213,1230,1252]" captionTargetBox="[155,1099,175,1194]" captionTargetId="figure-87@6.[146,1104,165,1194]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="Figure 2. (A–D) Zyzzogeton guatemalensis sp. nov., male holotype. (A) Pygofer, subgenital plate, and anal tube, lateral view. (B) Genital capsule, ventral view. (C) Connective and style, dorsal view. (D) Aedeagus, lateral view. (E–G) Zyzzogeton haenschi Breddin, female. (E) Abdominal sternite VII, ventral view. (F) Pygofer and anal tube, lateral view. (G) Second valvula of ovipositor, general lateral view. BHA: basal hyaline area, RPL: subrectangular pygofer lobe. (Scale bars: 1 mm.)" figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4593935" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4593935/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="1643">Figures 2</figureCitation>
A–D) much as in 
<taxonomicName authority="Mejdalani &amp; Costa &amp; Carvalho, 2008" authorityName="Mejdalani &amp; Costa &amp; Carvalho" authorityYear="2008" box="[929,1067,811,835]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Zyzzogeton" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="1643" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="emmrichi" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[929,1067,811,835]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="1643">Z. emmrichi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[1077,1169,810,834]" pageId="5" pageNumber="1643" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
Head with each ocellus distinctly closer to adjacent eye angle than to median line of crown. Forewings without a membranous area; veins clearly distinct. Styles (
<figureCitation box="[220,336,906,930]" captionStart="Figure 2" captionStartId="6.[146,213,1230,1252]" captionTargetBox="[155,1099,175,1194]" captionTargetId="figure-87@6.[146,1104,165,1194]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="Figure 2. (A–D) Zyzzogeton guatemalensis sp. nov., male holotype. (A) Pygofer, subgenital plate, and anal tube, lateral view. (B) Genital capsule, ventral view. (C) Connective and style, dorsal view. (D) Aedeagus, lateral view. (E–G) Zyzzogeton haenschi Breddin, female. (E) Abdominal sternite VII, ventral view. (F) Pygofer and anal tube, lateral view. (G) Second valvula of ovipositor, general lateral view. BHA: basal hyaline area, RPL: subrectangular pygofer lobe. (Scale bars: 1 mm.)" figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4593935" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4593935/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="1643">Figure 2C</figureCitation>
), in dorsal view, with apical half (behind outer lobe) elongate, narrow, and directed inwards. Apex of aedeagus (
<figureCitation box="[701,820,938,962]" captionStart="Figure 2" captionStartId="6.[146,213,1230,1252]" captionTargetBox="[155,1099,175,1194]" captionTargetId="figure-87@6.[146,1104,165,1194]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="Figure 2. (A–D) Zyzzogeton guatemalensis sp. nov., male holotype. (A) Pygofer, subgenital plate, and anal tube, lateral view. (B) Genital capsule, ventral view. (C) Connective and style, dorsal view. (D) Aedeagus, lateral view. (E–G) Zyzzogeton haenschi Breddin, female. (E) Abdominal sternite VII, ventral view. (F) Pygofer and anal tube, lateral view. (G) Second valvula of ovipositor, general lateral view. BHA: basal hyaline area, RPL: subrectangular pygofer lobe. (Scale bars: 1 mm.)" figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4593935" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4593935/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="1643">Figure 2D</figureCitation>
), in lateral view, with pair of broad dorsal processes directed ventrally, each process with two spiniform projections, one directed anteriorly and the other ventrally.
</paragraph>
