<paragraph blockId="5.[213,334,1234,1258]" box="[213,334,1234,1258]" pageId="5" pageNumber="1643">
<emphasis box="[213,334,1234,1258]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="1643">Etymology</emphasis>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="5.[213,1169,1274,1330]" pageId="5" pageNumber="1643">
The species epithet refers to the country of origin of the 
<typeStatus box="[864,967,1274,1298]" pageId="5" pageNumber="1643">holotype</typeStatus>
, which represents now the northernmost known record of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Breddin" authorityYear="1902" box="[680,809,1306,1330]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Zyzzogeton" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="1643" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[680,809,1306,1330]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="1643">Zyzzogeton</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
